fect the estimates that are so hotly debated today. Using Canada as their focal point, the authors look specifically at the impact of emission reduction policies on energy prices, technology options, and lifestyle choices. The book concludes with concrete proposals for overcoming the constraints of environmental policy making and the high initial costs of action. Policy makers need to know as much as possible about the costs of taking action to reduce greenhouse gas emissions. As indispensable as this book will be to policy analysts, it is also an important primer for a wider range of readers interested in the economic implications of climate change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aClimatic changesxGovernment policyzCanada. 0aEnvironmental policyxEconomic aspectszCanada. 0aEnvironmental protectionxEconomic aspectszCanada. 0aGreenhouse gas mitigationxEconomic aspectszCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh1 aNyboer, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSadownik, Bryn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485027840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774850278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774850278/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGr